abstract: Former Vice President Joe Biden is healthy enough to undertake the duties of the U.S. presidency, his doctor said on Tuesday in a health report released by the Democrat's campaign.
snippet: Former Vice President Joe Biden is healthy enough to undertake the duties of the U.S. presidency, his doctor said on Tuesday in a health report released by the Democrat's campaign.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Former Vice President Joe Biden is healthy enough to undertake the duties of the U.S. presidency, his doctor said on Tuesday in a health report released by the Democrat's campaign.
headline_main: Biden, 77, Is Healthy and Fit to Serve as President, His Doctor Says
headline_print_headline: Biden, 77, Is Healthy and Fit to Serve as President, His Doctor Says

abstract: During a seven-event swing in southeastern Iowa over the past several days, Democratic U.S. presidential contender Elizabeth Warren took more than 60 questions from voters on everything from sustainable farming to Medicare for All.
snippet: During a seven-event swing in southeastern Iowa over the past several days, Democratic U.S. presidential contender Elizabeth Warren took more than 60 questions from voters on everything from sustainable farming to Medicare for All.
lead_paragraph: KEOKUK, Iowa — During a seven-event swing in southeastern Iowa over the past several days, Democratic U.S. presidential contender Elizabeth Warren took more than 60 questions from voters on everything from sustainable farming to Medicare for All.
headline_main: On the 2020 Campaign Trail, Little Talk of Impeachment Ahead of Historic Vote
headline_print_headline: On the 2020 Campaign Trail, Little Talk of Impeachment Ahead of Historic Vote

abstract: OxyContin maker Purdue Pharma shouldn't give its CEO a bonus next year as the company goes through bankruptcy and tries to settle 2,700 lawsuits over the opioid crisis, 11 U.S. senators said in a letter Tuesday.
snippet: OxyContin maker Purdue Pharma shouldn't give its CEO a bonus next year as the company goes through bankruptcy and tries to settle 2,700 lawsuits over the opioid crisis, 11 U.S. senators said in a letter Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — OxyContin maker Purdue Pharma shouldn't give its CEO a bonus next year as the company goes through bankruptcy and tries to settle 2,700 lawsuits over the opioid crisis, 11 U.S. senators said in a letter Tuesday.
headline_main: 11 Senators Ask Purdue Pharma Not to Give CEO a Bonus
headline_print_headline: 11 Senators Ask Purdue Pharma Not to Give CEO a Bonus

abstract: The enormous defense bill, one of the most expensive in the nation’s history, contains a litany of bipartisan rebukes to Russia, Turkey and China.
snippet: The enormous defense bill, one of the most expensive in the nation’s history, contains a litany of bipartisan rebukes to Russia, Turkey and China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate on Tuesday voted overwhelmingly to pass a bipartisan $738 billion defense policy bill, sending President Trump one of the most expensive military measures in the nation’s history and one that he has championed as a critical priority.

abstract: The Democrats' next primary debate will proceed as scheduled this week, the Democratic National Committee announced Tuesday, after the party stepped in to help arrange a settlement to a labor dispute that had threatened the forum.
snippet: The Democrats' next primary debate will proceed as scheduled this week, the Democratic National Committee announced Tuesday, after the party stepped in to help arrange a settlement to a labor dispute that had threatened the forum.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democrats' next primary debate will proceed as scheduled this week, the Democratic National Committee announced Tuesday, after the party stepped in to help arrange a settlement to a labor dispute that had threatened the forum.
headline_main: Democratic Debate to Proceed After Labor Agreement Reached
headline_print_headline: Democratic Debate to Proceed After Labor Agreement Reached

abstract: Cafeteria workers at the debate site enlisted the candidates’ support as they fought successfully for a better contract. The candidates had said they would not cross a picket line to participate.
snippet: Cafeteria workers at the debate site enlisted the candidates’ support as they fought successfully for a better contract. The candidates had said they would not cross a picket line to participate.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The next Democratic presidential debate will go on as scheduled Thursday, after negotiators on Tuesday reached agreement in a labor dispute that had threatened to upend the event while highlighting organized labor’s influence with the leading Democratic presidential candidates.

abstract: Michael R. Bloomberg is showing what a virtually bottomless advertising budget can do by buying his way into the hottest political conversations of the moment.
snippet: Michael R. Bloomberg is showing what a virtually bottomless advertising budget can do by buying his way into the hottest political conversations of the moment.
lead_paragraph: Type the word “impeachment” into Google, and odds are the first search result won’t offer a news report on the latest developments in Washington.

abstract: It’s natural for a rising candidate to get kicked around. But the nature of the backlash says a lot about the past decade of Democratic politics.
snippet: It’s natural for a rising candidate to get kicked around. But the nature of the backlash says a lot about the past decade of Democratic politics.
lead_paragraph: Last month, after polls showed Pete Buttigieg vaulting unexpectedly to the lead in Iowa’s Democratic caucus, he aired an ad introducing his plan for higher-education reform: a proposal to make public-college tuition free for households earning up to $100,000 a year and reduce it on a sliding scale for those making up to $150,000. “Some voices,” he says in the ad, want to make college “free, even for the kids of millionaires” — a swipe at his rivals to the left, Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders, who had each called for free college for all.

abstract: U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg pledged on Monday to end the Trump administration's "discriminatory policies" toward Latinos, as the South Bend, Indiana, mayor looks for ways to boost his appeal among minority voters.
snippet: U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg pledged on Monday to end the Trump administration's "discriminatory policies" toward Latinos, as the South Bend, Indiana, mayor looks for ways to boost his appeal among minority voters.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg pledged on Monday to end the Trump administration's "discriminatory policies" toward Latinos, as the South Bend, Indiana, mayor looks for ways to boost his appeal among minority voters.
headline_main: Buttigieg Pledges 'New Era' for U.S. Latinos in Push for Minority Voters
